                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="318930" author="adilger" created="Tue, 23 Nov 2021 00:35:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This happens intermittently with ZFS-based systems when the VM is stalled, possibly because other VMs are doing heavy IO to the host.  It looks like the tuning to increase the fail retry count is missing on the new test cluster and needs to be applied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better if ZFS MMP handled this more gracefully, by resuming (and verifying MMP has not been modified) if the IO completes.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
